The Norwegian Institute for Public Health coordinated a study on the development of motors of children whose mothers were treated with SSRI, analyzing data of 51 404 children from the Norwegian cohort study of mother and child, researching the effects of using SSRI for the development of motor skills at the age of 3 years.
